.TH "hgafb_setcolreg" 9 "hgafb_setcolreg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hgafb_setcolreg \- set color registers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hgafb_setcolreg
.BI "(u_int regno "  ","
.BI "u_int red "  ","
.BI "u_int green "  ","
.BI "u_int blue "  ","
.BI "u_int transp "  ","
.BI "struct fb_info *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "regno" 12
register index to set
.IP "red" 12
red value, unused
.IP "green" 12
green value, unused
.IP "blue" 12
blue value, unused
.IP "transp" 12
transparency value, unused
.IP "info" 12
unused

This callback function is used to set the color registers of a HGA
board. Since we have only two fixed colors only \fIregno\fP is checked.
A zero is returned on success and 1 for failure.
